at VMI  Pat counsels students and parents concerning their individual situation and qualified need  and responds to correspondence  She is responsible for entering all aid  to include financial aid  athletic scholarships  ROTC scholarships  pre paid plans  and all outside awards for each student into the database for post view and billing  She is also the Veterans Representative and handles all of the paperwork in processing claims for veterans  dependents of veterans  and members of the guard  Pat has two daughters and four grandchildren  VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu 